    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indicator 1. Number of staff trained to respond to impacts of climate-related events (gender disaggregated).
Indicator 2. Number of people practising climate change adaptation technologies (gender disaggregated).
Indicator 3. Knowledge management centre strengthened through the support of project activities

1. # of staff trained to respond to impacts of climate-related events;
1.1.# of risk models developed;
1.2. Relevant threat and hazard information generated and disseminated to stakeholders on a timely basis;
1.3. Integrated catchment management strategy developed;
1.3.1. # of staff trained;
1.3.2.# of community members trained;
1.4. # of interactions between relevant stakeholders;
1.5. # of PES models developed for the KRB;
2. # of people practising climate change adaptation technologies;
2.1.1. Total # of men and women benefitting from reduced vulnerability to climate change;
2.1. # of extension service providers trained;
2.2. # of WAPs developed;
2.3. # of hectares of land with EbA activities implemented at project sites in each district;
3. Knowledge management centre strengthened through the support of project activities;
3.1. Existing knowledge centre/ platforms/ hubs in Tajikistan are supported and include information and data on KRB and specifically climate risk information;
3.2. Evaluation of EbA interventions in target sites conducted.</narrative>
